## 1. Tech Stack & Boundaries (DO NOT BREAK)
- Frontend: React, TypeScript, Vite, Tailwind CSS, Zod.
- Backend: Node.js, Express, Prisma (v5), PostgreSQL, Genkit.
- Integration Layer: NEVER modify `frontend/src/services/apiClient.ts` or `frontend/src/services/signalService.ts`. The API contracts are strictly locked.
- Database Schema: NEVER modify `backend/prisma/schema.prisma` without explicit permission.
- Data Privacy: Do NOT persist `image_base64` or `raw_message` to the database or add them to the Zod EnrichedSignal schema. Images are session-local only.
- Styling: The app uses a dark "command-center" aesthetic. Do NOT implement Light Mode. Use Tailwind CSS exclusively.

## 2. Project Execution & Architecture
- Zero Assumptions: Always ask targeted clarifying questions regarding scale, scope, and use case before executing a large prompt. Never infer parameters.
- Phased Execution: Break complex requests into modular phases. Execute one phase at a time and wait for user confirmation.
- Logic Preservation: Do not modify core business logic during refactoring unless explicitly requested.

## 3. Development & Engineering Standards
- Self-Documenting Code: Break code into single-responsibility functions/classes with clear, descriptive names.
- Standardized Docstrings: Use JSDoc for JS/TS for all functions, classes, and modules to define arguments, return types, and core purpose.
- The "Why" Comments: Use 1-to-2-line block comments exclusively to explain complex business logic or architectural decisions. Do not explain basic syntax.
- Security & Error Handling: Implement robust error handling (try/catch, AppError). No hardcoded keys.
- Output & Logging: Suppress granular logs. Use the standard `logger` library rather than `console.log`.

## 4. The "Self-Healing" Protocol (Cursor Edition)
- Read Before Write: Always read the relevant files in the codebase before proposing modifications to ensure you understand the current state and architecture.
- Strict Dependency Tracking: Before suggesting a new NPM package, read `package.json` to check current dependencies and versions.
- Context Check: At the end of every major architectural change, list the files modified to verify state alignment.
- Commit Messaging: Provide an industry-standard Conventional Commit message (e.g., `feat(ui): implement victim view toggle`) summarizing the work after a full phase is completed and approved.